00:07:02.070 --> 00:07:05.309
we designed the full hardware
and software stack ourselves.

00:07:05.309 --> 00:07:07.350
And this allowed us to
focus on important details

00:07:07.350 --> 00:07:12.540
like battery life, camera
quality, and UI consistency.

00:07:12.540 --> 00:07:14.310
The response has been
fantastic, and we're

00:07:14.310 --> 00:07:15.685
really proud of
the quality built

00:07:15.685 --> 00:07:17.190
into each of the products.

00:07:17.190 --> 00:07:19.560
And we don't just keep the
improvements for ourselves.

00:07:19.560 --> 00:07:22.260
Android N is open source and
it's the best mobile operating

00:07:22.260 --> 00:07:24.960
system we've ever
built. This year,

00:07:24.960 --> 00:07:26.820
Google is still
investing heavily

00:07:26.820 --> 00:07:29.124
in performance and
polish for Android.

00:07:29.124 --> 00:07:31.290
And we look forward to
sharing more details with you

00:07:31.290 --> 00:07:36.070
later this year when
we announce Android O.

00:07:36.070 --> 00:07:38.170
The Play Store team
has been laser-focused

00:07:38.170 --> 00:07:40.510
on improving the quality
of the user experience,

00:07:40.510 --> 00:07:43.690
both within the store and
within the apps and games that

00:07:43.690 --> 00:07:45.430
are downloaded from Play.

00:07:45.430 --> 00:07:47.980
About a billion users
come to the Play Store

00:07:47.980 --> 00:07:50.570
every month to learn
about apps and games.

00:07:50.570 --> 00:07:52.240
And so we run hundreds
of experiments

00:07:52.240 --> 00:07:54.490
to optimize their experience.

00:07:54.490 --> 00:07:58.540
Optimize the store for us
has meant growing downloads

00:07:58.540 --> 00:08:00.130
by putting the
right game in front

00:08:00.130 --> 00:08:02.800
of the right user in
the right context.

00:08:02.800 --> 00:08:04.930
And this is still
true, but we're

00:08:04.930 --> 00:08:08.362
rethinking what right game
and right context means.

00:08:08.362 --> 00:08:09.820
We don't really
think a user should

00:08:09.820 --> 00:08:13.150
have to download 20
games before finding one

00:08:13.150 --> 00:08:14.760
that she really likes.

00:08:14.760 --> 00:08:17.350
And so this year, we've
begun tuning our algorithms

00:08:17.350 --> 00:08:22.570
to optimize for user
engagement, not just downloads.

00:08:22.570 --> 00:08:25.480
So for example, a title that
gets a whole bunch of downloads

00:08:25.480 --> 00:08:29.270
because it has a catchy icon,
but is then quickly uninstalled

00:08:29.270 --> 00:08:31.630
will receive less
prominence than a title

00:08:31.630 --> 00:08:35.716
that drives true user
engagement and retention.

00:08:35.716 --> 00:08:37.299
We're also working
on several features

00:08:37.299 --> 00:08:42.059
to improve the prominence and
conversion for premium games.

00:08:42.059 --> 00:08:43.710
A lot of these are
really high quality,

00:08:43.710 --> 00:08:45.720
but they have to overcome
this extra hurdle

00:08:45.720 --> 00:08:47.075
of upfront payment.

00:08:47.075 --> 00:08:49.200
The first of these features
we're announcing today,

00:08:49.200 --> 00:08:51.810
and we're calling it
strikethrough pricing,

00:08:51.810 --> 00:08:53.490
you can use
strikethrough pricing

00:08:53.490 --> 00:08:56.040
to run a price promotion
on a premium app or game

00:08:56.040 --> 00:08:58.260
in the Google Play Store.

00:08:58.260 --> 00:09:01.740
Promotions drive awareness,
conversion, and a sense

00:09:01.740 --> 00:09:03.570
of value for our users.

00:09:03.570 --> 00:09:05.040
Here's how it works.

00:09:05.040 --> 00:09:07.210
Any of you can log into
the Developer Console

00:09:07.210 --> 00:09:10.080
today and set up a
promotion on your game.

00:09:10.080 --> 00:09:12.480
You just tell us what
discount you want to apply,

00:09:12.480 --> 00:09:15.750
when you want to apply
it, and we do the rest.

00:09:15.750 --> 00:09:18.840
Users will see the original and
discounted price on the home

00:09:18.840 --> 00:09:23.310
page, in the search results,
and in the app listing page.

00:09:23.310 --> 00:09:25.380
In our early pilot
phase, developers

00:09:25.380 --> 00:09:29.820
saw a lift in installs
ranging from 3x to 20x

00:09:29.820 --> 00:09:32.730
when running a
promotion on their game.

00:09:32.730 --> 00:09:34.770
Many of the developers
saw a sustained uplift

00:09:34.770 --> 00:09:39.000
in performance, even after
the discount had ended.

00:09:39.000 --> 00:09:43.680
So we're really excited
about the progress so far.

00:09:43.680 --> 00:09:46.020
Now obviously, there
is a correlation

00:09:46.020 --> 00:09:50.160
between the size of the discount
and the level of marketing

00:09:50.160 --> 00:09:52.450
spend that you do, and
the size of the uplift.

00:09:52.450 --> 00:09:54.908
But across the board, results
have been really encouraging,

00:09:54.908 --> 00:09:57.340
and we'd like to see more of
you using this feature soon.

00:09:57.340 --> 00:10:00.450
And throughout the year,
you'll see additional features

00:10:00.450 --> 00:10:03.480
meant to drive more prominence
conversion for premium games

00:10:03.480 --> 00:10:06.480
as we work to create a healthy
ecosystem of developers,

00:10:06.480 --> 00:10:07.560
players, and pairs.

00:10:10.170 --> 00:10:12.360
Another way we'll be
highlighting quality games

00:10:12.360 --> 00:10:14.760
on Android is through
our new editorial pages

00:10:14.760 --> 00:10:17.070
which are launching in Q2.

00:10:17.070 --> 00:10:19.710
These pages allow Play
editors to showcase

00:10:19.710 --> 00:10:23.160
magical, high-performing
Android games.

00:10:23.160 --> 00:10:25.080
You can think of them
as a handcrafted page

00:10:25.080 --> 00:10:26.840
built around a theme.

00:10:26.840 --> 00:10:29.810
In this example, we've made
a page for roleplaying games.

00:10:29.810 --> 00:10:32.220
Up top, we show an introduction
to the genre, followed

00:10:32.220 --> 00:10:34.761
by a short list of titles
that have earned our love,

00:10:34.761 --> 00:10:36.510
along with the reasons
why we picked them.

