00:39:52.160 --> 00:39:55.640
Now a lot of you know that
indies are very near and dear

00:39:55.640 --> 00:39:57.570
to our hearts.

00:39:57.570 --> 00:40:01.350
They risk everything for
innovation and expression,

00:40:01.350 --> 00:40:03.480
and bring a richer
diversity of delight

00:40:03.480 --> 00:40:06.750
to everyone on their
platform of choice.

00:40:06.750 --> 00:40:09.060
We work hard to make
sure that indies have

00:40:09.060 --> 00:40:12.330
a home on Google Play, too.

00:40:12.330 --> 00:40:16.260
Last year on this stage, we
announced the Indie Corner.

00:40:16.260 --> 00:40:19.830
This dedicated page
on the Play Store

00:40:19.830 --> 00:40:22.920
highlights fresh new launches,
as well as proven indie

00:40:22.920 --> 00:40:24.570
masterpieces.

00:40:24.570 --> 00:40:26.490
We're excited to see
the program continue

00:40:26.490 --> 00:40:30.600
to grow after featuring
over 250 games

00:40:30.600 --> 00:40:34.770
and driving millions of
installs in its first year.

00:40:34.770 --> 00:40:36.990
And we were just getting
started with that.

00:40:36.990 --> 00:40:39.000
Since then, we've
tested new ways

00:40:39.000 --> 00:40:43.440
to discover and support indies
by hosting our first indie game

00:40:43.440 --> 00:40:49.110
festivals and contests for
developers across the world--

00:40:49.110 --> 00:40:53.040
in Seoul, San Francisco,
and two weeks ago in London.

00:40:53.040 --> 00:40:54.870
Keep your eyes open
for more efforts

00:40:54.870 --> 00:40:57.780
like these throughout the year.

00:40:57.780 --> 00:41:00.510
Now we're committed
to helping indies grow

00:41:00.510 --> 00:41:03.490
on Android and Google Play.

00:41:03.490 --> 00:41:08.770
The dedication and passion
you have is incredible.

00:41:08.770 --> 00:41:12.600
And we thank you
for your commitment.

00:41:12.600 --> 00:41:15.450
Given this instinct to
innovate, indies are frequently

00:41:15.450 --> 00:41:18.360
the first to experiment
and find new ways to bring

00:41:18.360 --> 00:41:21.390
new ideas to new platforms.

00:41:21.390 --> 00:41:25.450
And they're willing to open
perspectives through empathy.

00:41:25.450 --> 00:41:27.250
It's then with a
special pleasure

00:41:27.250 --> 00:41:31.120
to share and reveal a game that
hits all of our hot buttons,

00:41:31.120 --> 00:41:34.310
including social
and persistence.

00:41:34.310 --> 00:41:36.770
From our friends at
Spry Fox, please join me

00:41:36.770 --> 00:41:38.610
in welcoming Daniel Cook.

00:41:38.610 --> 00:41:43.110
[APPLAUSE]

00:41:47.110 --> 00:41:49.260
DANIEL COOK: Hello everyone.

00:41:49.260 --> 00:41:53.460
So Spry Fox has been making
little tiny games for years.

00:41:53.460 --> 00:41:55.980
"Triple Town," "Alphabear,"
"Realm of the Mad God,"

00:41:55.980 --> 00:41:57.300
"Bushido Bear."

00:41:57.300 --> 00:42:02.900
Last June we started thinking
about our very first VR game.

00:42:02.900 --> 00:42:04.830
We had a couple of goals.

00:42:04.830 --> 00:42:09.290
First, we wanted to build a
home for the Spry Fox bears.

00:42:09.290 --> 00:42:12.260
Millions of people have
played these characters,

00:42:12.260 --> 00:42:13.742
and they absolutely adore them.

00:42:13.742 --> 00:42:15.200
But we've never
really had a chance

00:42:15.200 --> 00:42:19.010
to build out the world
in which they live.

00:42:19.010 --> 00:42:21.630
Second, and probably
more importantly,

00:42:21.630 --> 00:42:24.470
to be quite honest,
is we wanted to build

00:42:24.470 --> 00:42:27.890
something that was positive,
something that we could maybe

00:42:27.890 --> 00:42:31.460
counteract a lot of the really
horrendous negativity that's

00:42:31.460 --> 00:42:34.700
been swirling around
the world lately.

00:42:34.700 --> 00:42:37.960
So we started dreaming.

00:42:37.960 --> 00:42:44.530
What if we could build
a nice gaming community?

00:42:44.530 --> 00:42:47.290
What if we could
make a game where

00:42:47.290 --> 00:42:52.120
everyone is encouraged to
be helpful, friendly and

00:42:52.120 --> 00:42:54.580
inclusive?

00:42:54.580 --> 00:42:58.290
So we've been working on
a big, beautiful game that

00:42:58.290 --> 00:43:00.030
does just that.

00:43:00.030 --> 00:43:02.188
We call it "Beartopia."

00:43:04.880 --> 00:43:08.330
"Beartopia" is an
honest-to-goodness game.

00:43:08.330 --> 00:43:12.710
Many VR experiences end up
being these sort of short demos.

00:43:12.710 --> 00:43:18.170
In "Beartopia," you play in
this rich, persistent world, one

00:43:18.170 --> 00:43:21.410
that you can come back
to every single day.

00:43:21.410 --> 00:43:24.260
"Beartopia" is multiplayer.

00:43:24.260 --> 00:43:27.050
Everyone lives together
in this amazing village.

00:43:27.050 --> 00:43:33.330
And you'll meet other players
and you'll build friendships.

00:43:33.330 --> 00:43:39.930
And finally, "Beartopia"
is completely co-operative.

00:43:39.930 --> 00:43:44.370
It is our firm belief
that every single game

00:43:44.370 --> 00:43:48.960
player is an immigrant
into the worlds we build.

00:43:48.960 --> 00:43:52.440
And we have a duty
as creators to ensure

00:43:52.440 --> 00:43:57.126
that our virtual communities
bring out the best in people.

00:43:57.126 --> 00:43:59.530
In "Beartopia,"
all the players are

00:43:59.530 --> 00:44:02.320
immigrants to this
lovely seaside village,

00:44:02.320 --> 00:44:04.590
coming there for the first time.

00:44:04.590 --> 00:44:07.060
And in this little
utopia, we've set it

00:44:07.060 --> 00:44:10.100
up so that everyone
can work together.

00:44:10.100 --> 00:44:14.420
Because we know that when we
mix different people from all

00:44:14.420 --> 00:44:21.580
walks of life, we build strong,
exciting, vibrant communities.

00:44:21.580 --> 00:44:25.140
So "Beartopia" is
something really special,

00:44:25.140 --> 00:44:27.580
and we really can't wait
to share it with you.

00:44:27.580 --> 00:44:29.950
Here is a very brief teaser.

00:44:29.950 --> 00:44:31.768
Thank you.

